I have always been a strong proponent of roleplaying, and fight for this playstyle on my own 99% non-RP server I play on most of the time. When I came to play on FV as well, I loved the new ruleset.<br>
<br>
I agree with the languages, the grouping restrictions, the /ooc removal, the range limit on /shout, and the single character per server rules wholeheartedly, as they promote this server and its distinct RP attitude and community.<br>
<br>
But even I, a stalwart of the RP aproach, find the permanent /roleplay setting, with no visibility of class/level, too much to bear. It is simply put, for those of us who do not want to be in large guilds, almost impossible to get balanced groups for anything, even at low level.<br>
<br>
This fact alone has made me more and more reluctant to play here, though I love this place in principle and the types who play here, because I can find groupmates on Lanys, even with my strict RP rules, far more easily than on FV, especially when I play (in European peak time, not American). I do not find being LFG and bored or soloing all the time fun AT ALL. I know very well, if this one thing were lifted, these problems would be wiped away.<br>
<br>
That is my take on this, anyway.<br>
<br>
Be well, everyone. And I will still be around (just more often on Lanys than here).<br>
<br>
/bow<br>
